description:
Sit alongside the existing requirements.schema.json in tools/uucd-core/schemas/. The two schemas have separate lifecycles:
- requirements.schema.json (existing) = WHAT we test. Per-category rows with verification methods.
- nfr-vector.schema.json (new) = HOW WE PRIORITIZED. The output of <nfr-compass>.

Shape:
{
  '$schema': '...',
  '$id': 'nfr-vector.schema.json',
  type: 'object',
  required: ['vector', 'rationales', 'costWeights', 'capacityPoints', 'capacitySource', 'decidedAt'],
  properties: {
    vector: {
      type: 'object',
      patternProperties: {
        '^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*$': { enum: ['critical', 'important', 'acceptable', 'not-relevant'] }
      }
    },
    rationales: {
      type: 'object',
      patternProperties: {
        '^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*$': { type: 'string', minLength: 10, maxLength: 200 }
      },
      description: 'Required for every ility marked critical.'
    },
    costWeights: {
      type: 'object',
      patternProperties: { '^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*$': { type: 'integer', minimum: 0 } },
      description: 'Frozen snapshot of the cost weights in effect when this vector was decided.'
    },
    capacityPoints: { type: 'integer', minimum: 1 },
    capacitySource: { enum: ['formula', 'manual'] },
    ironTriangleHash: { type: 'string', description: 'FNV-1a of the iron-triangle.json this vector was decided against.' },
    overrunRationale: { type: 'string', minLength: 10, maxLength: 400 },
    decidedAt: { type: 'string', format: 'date' },
    decidedBy: { type: 'string' },
    locked: { type: 'boolean', default: false },
    revisionLog: { type: 'array', items: { /* { revisedAt, revisedBy, changes:[{field, from, to, reason: minLength 10}] } */ } }
  }
}

Validator invariants beyond JSON Schema:
- For every ility with vector[ility] === 'critical', rationales MUST contain a key for that ility.
- Reject vectors where rationales references an ility not present in vector.
- Compute criticalSum = sum of costWeights[ility] for ility where vector[ility] === 'critical'. If criticalSum > capacityPoints, overrunRationale MUST be present and >=10 chars.

Depends on vanilla-breeze-0tr4 (nfr-compass — emits this exact shape) and vanilla-breeze-05y0 (iron-triangle — produces capacityPoints + ironTriangleHash this references).

Add a small additive API to the VBElement base class so components can flip CSS-targetable internal states via the CustomStateSet API. Pure addition — no existing attribute is removed or replaced.

## Context

See admin/specs/custom-state-set-research.md for the full analysis. Decision: additive adoption. This bead lands the helper. A follow-up bead pilots usage on 2-3 components.

## Implementation

1. Add to src/lib/vb-element.js:

   ```js
   #internals;

   /**
    * Toggle an internal CSS state. Use for component-private flags
    * targetable via the :state(name) selector. For author-facing state,
    * keep using data-* / aria-* attributes — see admin/specs/custom-state-set-research.md.
    * @param {string} name
    * @param {boolean} on
    */
   setState(name, on) {
     if (!this.#internals) this.#internals = this.attachInternals();
     const states = this.#internals.states;
     try {
       on ? states.add(name) : states.delete(name);
     } catch {
       // Legacy --name syntax for older Chromium/WebKit
       on ? states.add(`--${name}`) : states.delete(`--${name}`);
     }
   }

   /** Subclasses that already attached internals can hand them back. */
   _adoptInternals(internals) {
     if (!this.#internals) this.#internals = internals;
   }
   ```

2. Refactor the seven form-associated components that already call `attachInternals()` so they don't double-attach when `setState()` is later called on them. Pick ONE of:
   - (a) Drop the private `#internals` field on the subclass and use `this.attachInternals()` lazily through the base helper. Cleaner but touches each component's existing form-value/validity code.
   - (b) Have subclasses call `this._adoptInternals(this.attachInternals())` in their constructor. Minimal change, leaves existing code structure intact.

   Recommend (b) — narrow blast radius. Components: combo-box, date-picker, time-picker, calendar-wc, color-picker, chat-input, star-rating.

3. Unit test in tests/unit/ verifying:
   - setState('foo', true) makes el.matches(':state(foo)') true
   - setState('foo', false) flips it back
   - Works on a form-associated subclass that already attached internals (no double-attach throw)
   - Legacy --name path is hit when add() throws (mock or skip if unfeasible)

## Acceptance

- VBElement.setState lands with JSDoc
- Seven form-associated components refactored without behavior change (existing tests still green)
- Unit test for the helper passes in both projects (desktop + mobile)
- No public attribute removed; admin/syntax.md unchanged

## Out of scope

- Any actual use of setState() in components — that's bead 2
- Removing or migrating any existing data-* attribute — explicitly deferred per the spec doc

## Reference

- admin/specs/custom-state-set-research.md
- src/lib/vb-element.js — base class
- src/web-components/combo-box/logic.js:43,66 — representative form-associated pattern

The URL masking hook in src/lib/analytics.js (maskUrl() called from buildEnvelope()) accepts regex patterns but is never fed any. The docs site currently doesn't have sensitive per-user paths, so this is premature.

Add masks to window.vbAnalyticsConfig.urlMasks when the site grows paths like /admin/<user-id>/, /preview/<draft-id>/, or similar. Config shape:

  window.vbAnalyticsConfig = {
    urlMasks: [
      { pattern: /^\/admin\/[^/]+/, replace: '/admin/*' },
      { pattern: /^\/preview\/[0-9a-f]{8,}/, replace: '/preview/*' },
    ],
  };

Scope: not urgent. Close if/when the docs site grows such paths, or file a broader "analytics privacy review" issue.

Reference: admin/r-n-d/analytics/analytics-spec.md "URL Masking" section.
